blueprint/src/chapters/Picard_FunctorAb.tex:4:This chapter is the natural successor to Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_Functor}. The relative Picard functor of Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_Functor} is set-valued; the construction merely forgets the abelian-group structure that the values $\Pic(C \times_k S) / p_S^*\Pic(S)$ carry by definition. To set up Phase~C step~3 (\'etale sheafification) and any future cohomology-of-Picard-presheaf work, we need an abelian-group-valued variant whose values agree on the nose with the set-valued ones.
